      <div resp="part:emfr" type="translation">
        <p n="1">Prosperity! Fortune!</p>
        <p n="1">Twentieth year of the victorious king Kampavarman.</p>
        <p n="1-5">The gold that <gap extent="unknown" reason="undefined" unit="character"></gap> Paṭṭāṉ, <supplied reason="subaudible">one</supplied> among the governing delegates <supplied reason="explanation">
            <foreign>āluṅ kaṇattār</foreign>
          </supplied> of Kāvatippākkam in the Paṭuvūrkkōṭṭam, has given so as to provide water in the glorious temple of Perumāṉaṭikaḷ <supplied reason="subaudible">in</supplied> Tiruppontai in Rājamallaccaturvecimaṅgala: eleven <foreign>kaḻañcu</foreign>s.</p>
        <p n="5">With the interest coming from this gold, I have given so as to provide water.</p>
        <p n="5-6">The dust from the glorious feet of he who protects this pious act are on my head.</p>
